 \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n                \n    \n    \n        \n    \n\n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n            \n    \n    \n                                                        \n                                \n                                \n                                                \n            \n        \n    \n        \n                                                                                                                                                                                                        \n            \n    \n    \n        \n                \n                    \n                        \n                                    \u003cdiv id=\"article-body\" itemprop=\"articleBody\"\u003e\u003cp\u003eOne of the best ChatGPT alternatives is getting even better. Anthropic, the developer behind Claude, has announced the arrival of Voice Mode to its mobile apps. This should give you even more ways to interact with Claude from your phone.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"you-can-finally-talk-to-claude-on-your-phone\"\u003e\n                        You Can Finally Talk to Claude on Your Phone\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eVoice Mode is still rolling out in beta on mobile devices. At the time of writing, I haven\u0026#39;t yet found it in the Claude app on any of my devices.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eTo check if you have access to Voice Mode, you simply need to open the Claude app on your phone—install it from the \u003ca href=\"https://www.anrdoezrs.net/links/7251228/type/dlg/sid/UUmuoUeUpU2036766/https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.anthropic.claude\u0026amp;pli=1\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow sponsored\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eGoogle Play Store\u003c/a\u003e or the \u003ca href=\"https://apps.apple.com/us/app/claude-by-anthropic/id6473753684\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer nofollow\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eApple App Store\u003c/a\u003e if you haven\u0026#39;t yet—and then load up a chat.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eIf you have access to Voice mode, you\u0026#39;ll see what looks like a wavelength icon in the bottom right of the chat. It should be located next to the microphone icon you use for speech to text.\u003c/p\u003e    \n    \n    \n    \n\u003cp\u003eClaude\u0026#39;s new Voice mode is available for both free and paid users of the language model. Paid users will also be able to use Claude\u0026#39;s Voice mode to access their Google Docs, Calendar, Gmail, and other web searches using voice conversations.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eJust like ChatGPT\u0026#39;s Voice mode, which \u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/chatgpt-advanced-voice-feature-rolling-out-to-users/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eOpenAI released late last year\u003c/a\u003e, you can easily switch between both voice and text chat modes seamlessly. Anthropic says that previous context is also carried over in between modes and you can choose between five different voices.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003ch2 id=\"limited-availability\"\u003e\n                        Limited Availability\n               \u003c/h2\u003e\u003cp\u003eAnthropic says that Claude\u0026#39;s Voice mode is available in English within all of its mobile apps. It\u0026#39;s unclear yet when or if it will be available in other languages.\u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe company also says that those using the free version of Claude can expect around 20–30 messages before they have to wait for their session limits to reset, according to an \u003ca href=\"https://support.anthropic.com/en/articles/11101966-using-voice-mode-on-claude-mobile-apps?s=09\" target=\"_blank\"\u003eupdated support document\u003c/a\u003e. While that might not sound like a lot, it should at least let you try out the feature to see how useful you find it. Those with a paid Claude plan will be able to take advantage of the feature for longer periods of time.\u003c/p\u003e            \n    \n                    \n                        \n    \n    \n                                        \n    \n        \n    \n        \n                \n        \n    \u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"fa0a-452d-b3960ab9408b\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\n        \n        \n                        \t                \n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.makeuseof.com/reasons-use-claude-instead-of-chatgpt/\"\u003e\n\t\n\t\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.makeuseofimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/03/claude-and-chatgpt-icons-on-smartphone-screen.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\n\n            \n\n\n\n\n\u003cfigure\u003e\n        \u003cpicture\u003e\n        \n                                        \n                                    \n                                                                                                                                                                            \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003c